Constructor Detail

CaptureGroup

public CaptureGroup(List<? extends T> items,
                    int startIndex)
Creates a new CaptureGroup.

Parameters:
items - the List of items from which to capture; must not be null and must not be empty
startIndex - the zero-based index at which capturing will start; must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than items.size()
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if items is null or items is empty or startIndex is less than 0 or startIndex is greater than or equal to items.size()
Method Detail

getItems

public final List<? extends T> getItems()
Returns a non-null unmodifiable List of the items this CaptureGroup captured.

Returns:
a non-null List of items captured by this CaptureGroup. The List returned is that returned by the List.subList(int, int) method (or Collections.emptyList())

setEndIndex

public final void setEndIndex(int endIndex)
Sets the exclusive zero-based index that marks the end of the items this CaptureGroup will capture.

Parameters:
endIndex - the exclusive zero-based end index; must be greater than 0, less than the value of the startIndex supplied at construction time and less than the size of the List of items supplied at construction time
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if endIndex is invalid

equals

public final boolean equals(Object other)
Returns true if the supplied Object is equal to this CaptureGroup. Two CaptureGroups are equal if their start and end indices are the same. Notably, the List of items supplied at construction time is deliberately excluded from consideration.
